." Manpage for smi-build-tasklist
.TH smi-build-tasklist 1 "March 2026" "setmy.info" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
smi-build-tasklist \- build a TASKLIST.md file from components
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B smi-build-tasklist
.I [CONTENT_FILE]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B smi-build-tasklist
command generates a
.I TASKLIST.md
file in the current directory. It combines an introduction, AI-generated profiles, and content sections.
.PP
The process follows these steps:
.IP 1. 2
If
.I AGENTS-INTRO.md
exists in the current directory, it is used as the starting content for
.IR TASKLIST.md .
Otherwise,
.I TASKLIST.md
is started as an empty file.
.IP 2. 2
If
.I ai.profiles
exists in the current directory, its content is read as a list of profiles. The
.BR ai (1)
command is then called with these profiles, fetching them from the remote knowledge
app, and the output is appended to
.IR TASKLIST.md .
Profile names may use the
.B name:cat1,cat2
syntax to request specific categories.
.IP 3. 2
If arguments are provided, each
.I CONTENT_FILE
is appended to
.IR TASKLIST.md .
If no arguments are provided, the command looks for
.I TASKLIST-CONTENT.md
and appends it if found.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I AGENTS-INTRO.md
Introduction section for the tasklist.
.TP
.I ai.profiles
Space-separated list of AI profiles to include.
.TP
.I TASKLIST-CONTENT.md
Default content section if no arguments are provided.
.TP
.I TASKLIST.md
The generated output file.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ai (1)
